2008-11-13 03:27  kelnos

	* NEWS, xfce4-settings-manager/xfce-settings-manager-dialog.c:
	  set dialog type hint to 'normal', since it really is just a
	  normal window, and should have a minimize action (bug 4596)

2008-11-11 18:42  kelnos

	* xfce4-settings-helper/workspaces.c:
	  make the workspaces helper multi-screen aware and fix compilation
	  with older versions of libwnck

2008-11-11 05:17  kelnos

	* xfce4-settings-helper/workspaces.c:
	  oops, fix warning

2008-11-11 05:14  kelnos

	* xfce4-settings-helper/workspaces.c:
	  fix workspace names setting... seems wnck_workspace_change_name()
	  is broken if you call it several times in succession for
	  different workspaces

2008-11-11 05:14  kelnos

	* xfce4-settings-helper/main.c:
	  set SmRestartIfRunning if started in debug mode

2008-11-11 00:34  jannis

	* xfce4-settings-manager/Makefile.am,
	  xfce4-settings-manager/xfce-settings-manager-dialog.c,
	  xfce4-settings-manager/xfce-text-renderer.c,
	  xfce4-settings-manager/xfce-text-renderer.h:
	  Add XfceTextRenderer which is a copy of ThunarTextRenderer just
	  without the edit functionality. Use this renderer in the main
	  settings dialog so that we now have full prelit/follow-state and
	  keyboard navigation support. This fixes bug #4593.

2008-11-10 17:00  jannis

	* xfce4-settings-manager/main.c,
	  xfce4-settings-manager/xfce-settings-manager-dialog.c,
	  xfce4-settings-manager/xfce-settings-manager-dialog.h:
	  Implement --dialog=<dialog name> option in the settings manager.
	  This means you can now start it with e.g. "xfce4-settings-manager
	  --dialog xfce-ui-settings" and it will immediately switch to the
	  UI contents. Maybe we can make this the default for the Exec
	  field of all settings dialogs and add use special X-XfceExec
	  field for the *real* command which is then used by the settings
	  manager to launch the dialogs.
	  
	  Also fix a few occurances of GtkIconView/GTK_ICON_VIEW in the
	  code and set the "follow-state" property of the icon renderer to
	  TRUE so that the icons are properly prelighted on on mouse hover
	  events.

2008-11-10 06:31  stephan

	* xfsettingsd/registry.c:
	  Set some comments inside the registry file to hold others from
	  'fixing' defaults

2008-11-10 06:26  stephan

	* configure.ac.in, xfsettingsd/Makefile.am, xfsettingsd/registry.c,
	  xfsettingsd/xsettings.xml:
	  Bump version and dependency versions Fix bug 4545 the way it's
	  supposed to

