2008-10-18 21:58  jannis

	* Makefile.am, common, common/Makefile.am,
	  common/xfce-shortcuts-grabber.c, common/xfce-shortcuts-grabber.h,
	  common/xfce-shortcuts-provider.c,
	  common/xfce-shortcuts-provider.h, configure.ac.in,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/Makefile.am,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts-dialog.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts-provider.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts-provider.h,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts.h,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/xfce-keyboard-settings.c,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/Makefile.am,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/frap-shortcuts-provider.c,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/frap-shortcuts-provider.h,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/frap-shortcuts.c,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/frap-shortcuts.h,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/keyboard-shortcuts.c:
	  Properly handle keyboard layout changes in the shortcuts code.
	  This commit also introduces the common/ subdirectory containing
	  code used in several places. FrapShortcutsProvider is now
	  XfceShortcutsProvider. There's a new class XfceShortcutsGrabber
	  for grabbing key combinations and handling keyboard layout
	  changes. The GDK/X11-related code for the shortcuts has been
	  significantly simplified and is inspired by the code we had in
	  4.4.

