2008-10-07 12:31  jannis

	* dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts-provider.c,
	  po/POTFILES.in, xfce4-settings-helper/Makefile.am,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/frap-shortcuts-provider.c,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/frap-shortcuts-provider.h,
	  xfce4-settings-helper/keyboard-shortcuts.c:
	  Redo the settings helper to support FrapShortcutsProvider. Fix
	  warnings.

2008-10-07 04:51  jannis

	* dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts.c.bak:
	  Remove backup file.

2008-10-07 04:51  jannis

	* configure.ac.in, dialogs/keyboard-settings/Makefile.am,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts-dialog.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts-dialog.h,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts-provider.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts-provider.h,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts.c.bak,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/frap-shortcuts.h,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/keyboard-dialog.glade,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/main.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/xfce-keyboard-settings.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/xfce-keyboard-settings.h:
	  Re-implement the way keyboard shortcuts work.
	  
	  Depend on the latest version of xfconf as it includes some bug
	  fixes we need for this to work.
	  
	  Add FrapShortcutsProvider which acts as an abstraction layer over
	  the /default and /custom storage details. A FrapShortCutsProvider
	  represents a set of shortcuts, /commands or /xfwm4 for instance.
	  It automatically clones the default settings when created (if
	  necessary) and provides two signals: 'shortcut-removed' and
	  'shortcut-added'.
	  
	  Rework the conflicts dialog, add a reset button the the keyboard
	  settings dialog and make the whole settings dialog code a GObject
	  (XfceKeyboardSettings).

2008-10-06 21:59  stephan

	* xfce4-settings-editor/main_window.c,
	  xfce4-settings-editor/xfce4-settings-editor.glade:
	  Redid UI and refactored the code

2008-10-06 20:52  jannis

	* xfce4-settings-manager/xfce-settings-manager-dialog.c:
	  Add support for X-XfceHelpFile so dialogs can have a help button.
	  
	  X-XfceHelpFile is a new .desktop file key which allows dialogs to
	  hook into the help button of the main settings dialog. The main
	  dialog uses xfhelp4 to open relative X-XfceHelpFile's and
	  exo-open to open absolute filenames.

2008-10-06 20:52  jannis

	* xfce4-settings-helper/keyboard-shortcuts.c:
	  Introduce new way to separate default from custom shortcuts: Use
	  two different base properties ('/commands/default' and
	  '/commands/custom'). Use '/commands/default' by default and only
	  use the shortcuts defined in '/commands/custom' if
	  '/commands/custom/override' is TRUE.

2008-10-06 16:34  jari

	* po/ChangeLog, po/fi.po:
	  Update Finnish translations.

2008-10-05 23:17  stephan

	* xfce4-settings-editor/Makefile.am, xfce4-settings-editor/main.c,
	  xfce4-settings-editor/main_window.c,
	  xfce4-settings-editor/main_window.h,
	  xfce4-settings-editor/xfce4-settings-editor.glade:
	  Modify the GUI, put everything in the same treeview.

