2008-09-17 22:19  jannis

	* dialogs/accessibility-settings/main.c,
	  dialogs/appearance-settings/main.c,
	  dialogs/keyboard-settings/main.c, dialogs/mouse-settings/main.c,
	  xfce4-settings-manager/xfce-settings-manager-dialog.c:
	  Don't use kill() to make applications with embedded dialogs quit.
	  Instead, just destroy and re-create the socket. All clients now
	  have to connect to the 'delete-event' of their GtkPlug. In most
	  cases, just using gtk_main_quit() as a callback will work.

2008-09-17 07:34  stephan

	* xfsettingsd/registry.c:
	  fix little bug with wrong c/p

2008-09-17 07:30  stephan

	* xfsettingsd/registry.c:
	  add some missing XSETTINGS (hope moritz doesn't kill me)

